				<div class="comment-body"><p>We might suggest that if things are as in as much trouble as you suggest that people who are convinced that the Hugo Awards do not represent their wishes should club together and found a new award that does represent their wishes. As long as you do not use any of the registered service marks of the World Science Fiction Society to promote such an award, we have no objection to you doing so. Indeed, many of us would cheer you on for doing so.</p>
</div>

				<div class="reply">
				<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?replytocom=428331#respond' data-commentid="428331" data-postid="2391" data-belowelement="comment-428331" data-respondelement="respond" aria-label='Reply to Kevin'>Reply</a>				</div><!-- .reply -->
